		"name": "HireSmart Backend API Collection",
		"description": "## HireSmart API Collection\n\nComplete API collection for the HireSmart backend system. This collection includes endpoints for:\n\n### üîê Authentication\n- User registration and login (JWT)\n- Email verification\n- Password reset functionality\n- Profile management\n\n### üìö Reference Data (NEW!)\n- Skills, countries, states, cities, areas\n- Employment types and job statuses  \n- **Use these endpoints first** to get IDs needed for job creation\n\n### üè¢ Public Job Browsing\n- Browse available jobs (no authentication required)\n- Job search and filtering\n- Similar job recommendations\n\n### üëî Employer Features\n- Job posting and management\n- Application review and management\n- Candidate matching and discovery\n\n### üë§ Candidate Features\n- Resume upload and management\n- Job application management\n- Job recommendations\n- Application tracking\n\n### üõ† Admin Panel\n- System administration\n- User management\n- Analytics and reporting\n\n### üìù Workflow for Job Creation:\n1. **Get Reference Data**: Use `/reference/skills` and `/reference/countries` to get valid IDs\n2. **Get Location Hierarchy**: Use `/reference/states?country_id=X` ‚Üí `/reference/cities?state_id=X` ‚Üí `/reference/areas?city_id=X`\n3. **Create Job**: Use the IDs from steps 1-2 in your job posting\n\n### üîó Quick Links:\n- **Repository**: [GitHub](https://github.com/your-repo)\n- **Documentation**: [API Docs](https://your-docs-url)\n- **Postman Guide**: Check the POSTMAN_GUIDE.md file in the repository\n\n---\n\n**Environment Variables:**\n- `baseUrl`: Your API base URL (e.g., http://localhost:8000/api)\n- `token`: JWT token (auto-set after login)\n\n**Rate Limiting:**\nAll endpoints are rate-limited. Check individual endpoint descriptions for specific limits.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "üîê Authentication & Profile",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Register User",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    if (response.data && response.data.authorization.token) {",
									"        pm.environment.set('token', response.data.authorization.token);",
									"        console.log('Token saved:', response.data.authorization.token);",
									"    }",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"John Doe\",\n    \"email\": \"john.doe@example.com\",\n    \"password\": \"password123\",\n    \"password_confirmation\": \"password123\",\n    \"role\": \"candidate\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/register",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["auth", "register"]
						},
						"description": "Register a new user account. Role can be 'employer' or 'candidate'."
					}
				},
				{
					"name": "Verify Email",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    if (response.data && response.data.authorization.token) {",
									"        pm.environment.set('token', response.data.authorization.token);",
									"        pm.environment.set('userRole', response.data.user.role);",
									"        ",
									"        // Set role-specific tokens",
									"        if (response.data.user.role === 'employer') {",
									"            pm.environment.set('employerToken', response.data.authorization.token);",
									"        } else if (response.data.user.role === 'candidate') {",
									"            pm.environment.set('candidateToken', response.data.authorization.token);",
									"        } else if (response.data.user.role === 'admin') {",
									"            pm.environment.set('adminToken', response.data.authorization.token);",
									"        }",
									"        ",
									"        console.log('Email verified for user:', response.data.user.name, '- Role:', response.data.user.role);",
									"        console.log('Account is now active:', response.data.user.is_active);",
									"    }",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"email\": \"john.doe@example.com\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-email",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["auth", "verify-email"]
						},
						"description": "Verify user email address and activate account. Use the email address from registration. After verification, user will be able to login successfully."
					}
				},
